                <h1 style="color:#FFC900; text-align:center; font-size:50px; font-family:cursive;">Pancakes</h1>
                <img src="https://handletheheat.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/The-Best-Pancake-Recipe-SQUARE-500x375.jpg" height="500px"> 
                <h2 id="how to make">How to make it</h2>
                <h3 style="color:red;">You likely already have everything you need to make this pancake recipe. If not, here's what to add to your grocery list:</h3>
     <table style="font-size:20px;border:1px solid #4AE800; border-collapse:collapse">
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Ingredients</td>
            <td>Info</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Flour:</td>
            <td>This homemade pancake recipe starts with all-purpose flour</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Backing Powder:</td>
            <td> Baking powder, a leavener, is the secret to fluffy pancakes.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Sugar:</td>
            <td>Just a tablespoon of white sugar is all you'll need for subtly sweet pancakes.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Salt:</td>
            <td>A pinch of salt will enhance the overall flavor without making your pancakes taste salty.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Milk and Butter:</td>
            <td>Milk and butter add moisture and richness to the pancakes.</td>    
        </tr>
        <tr style="border:1px solid #4AE800; font-family:sans-serif;">
            <td>Eggs:</td>
            <td>A whole egg lends even more moisture. Plus, it helps bind the pancake batter together.</td> 
        </tr>       
    </table>               
                <h2 id="most famous in">Where it is mostly made in</h2>  
                <p style="color:green; font-size:20px;">In Uganda, pancakes are locally made with bananas (one of the staple foods of the country) and usually served as a breakfast or as a snack option. East Asia.</p>
